import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        subset = data[data['Series'] == series]
        ax.scatter(subset['X'], subset['Y'], label=series)
    
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.legend(title='Series')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y in each set of data?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mean_data = data.groupby('Series').mean()
    std_data = data.groupby('Series').std()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    mean_data.plot(kind='bar', y=['X', 'Y'], ax=ax, color=['blue', 'green'], label=['Mean X', 'Mean Y'])
    std_data.plot(kind='bar', y=['X', 'Y'], ax=ax, color=['red', 'orange'], label=['Std X', 'Std Y'], alpha=0.5)

    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each set of data?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Mean X', 'Mean Y', 'Std X', 'Std Y'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.xlabel('Series')
    plt.ylabel('Values')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    g = sns.FacetGrid(data, col="Series", hue="Series", col_wrap=2)
    g.map_dataframe(sns.histplot, x="X", kde=True, color="blue", label="X")
    g.map_dataframe(sns.histplot, x="Y", kde=True, color="red", label="Y")
    g.set_axis_labels("Value", "Frequency")
    g.add_legend(title="Variable")
    plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.85)
    g.fig.suptitle("What is the distribution of X and Y in each set of data?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for series in data['Series'].unique():
        subset = data[data['Series'] == series]
        ax.plot(subset['X'], subset['Y'], marker='o', linestyle='', label=series)
    
    ax.set_xlabel('X')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y')
    ax.legend(title='Series')
    plt.title('Is there a linear relationship between X and Y in each set of data?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 10))
    series_list = data['Series'].unique()
    
    for i, series in enumerate(series_list):
        ax = axes[i // 2, i % 2]
        subset = data[data['Series'] == series]
        sns.scatterplot(data=subset, x='X', y='Y', ax=ax, label=series)
        corr_coef = subset['X'].corr(subset['Y'])
        ax.axhline(y=corr_coef, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Correlation: {corr_coef:.2f}')
        ax.legend()
        ax.set_title(f'Series {series}')
    
    plt.suptitle("What is the correlation coefficient between X and Y in each set of data?", wrap=True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
